main event: A UFO sighting was reported by military personnel on May 14, 1961, over the East Indies.
interesting points: The object appeared as bright as a second magnitude star, The sighting lasted approximately 1.2 minutes, The object emitted an intermittent whine and a hissing sound upon disappearance, The object was seen traveling at a high rate of speed across the sky, The weather conditions were recorded as unknown, and it was lost in clouds on the horizon.
sighted object: a round white object resembling a bright star
witness description: military personnel from the US Navy and Air Force, including LCOL R.E. Dunlap, LCDR GA Murphy, LT R. Karger, LT G.E. King, LT MHS Walczak
